#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.2"
msgid "2. Nālandavagga"
msgstr "2. At Nālandā"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 20. Janapadakalyāṇīsutta → janapada (pts1)
msgctxt "sn47.20:0.3"
msgid "20. Janapadakalyāṇīsutta"
msgstr "20. The Finest Lady in the Land"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.170"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn47.20:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn47.20:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sumbhesu viharati sedakaṃ nāma sumbhānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sumbhas, near the town "
"of the Sumbhas called Sedaka."

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn47.20:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# Woodward and Thanissaro attribute the words to the crowd. I’m not sure which is correct, but I follow BB. See BB for notes on this and paramapasavani
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.20:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ‘janapadakalyāṇī, janapadakalyāṇī’ti kho, bhikkhave, "
"mahājanakāyo sannipateyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose that on hearing, ‘The finest lady in the land! The "
"finest lady in the land!’ a large crowd would gather."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘Sā kho panassa janapadakalyāṇī paramapāsāvinī nacce, paramapāsāvinī gīte."
msgstr ""
"And the finest lady in the land would dance and sing in a most thrilling way."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.3"
msgid ""
"Janapadakalyāṇī naccati gāyatī’ti kho, bhikkhave, bhiyyoso mattāya "
"mahājanakāyo sannipateyya."
msgstr ""
"On hearing, ‘The finest lady in the land is dancing and singing! The finest "
"lady in the land is dancing and singing!’ an even larger crowd would gather."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.4"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya jīvitukāmo amaritukāmo sukhakāmo dukkhappaṭikūlo."
msgstr ""
"Then a person would come along who wants to live and doesn’t want to die, "
"who wants to be happy and recoils from pain."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "They’d say to him:"

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ te, ambho purisa, samatittiko telapatto antarena ca mahāsamajjaṃ "
"antarena ca janapadakalyāṇiyā pariharitabbo."
msgstr ""
"‘Mister, this is a bowl full to the brim with oil. You must carry it in "
"between this large crowd and the finest lady in the land."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.7"
msgid "Puriso ca te ukkhittāsiko piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhissati."
msgstr "And a man with a drawn sword will follow behind you."

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.8"
msgid "Yattheva naṃ thokampi chaḍḍessati tattheva te siro pātessatī’ti."
msgstr "Wherever you spill even a drop, he’ll chop off your head right there.’"

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.9"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.10"
msgid ""
"api nu so puriso amuṃ telapattaṃ amanasikaritvā bahiddhā pamādaṃ āhareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would that person lose focus on that bowl, and negligently get distracted "
"outside?”"

msgctxt "sn47.20:2.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.1"
msgid "“Upamā kho myāyaṃ, bhikkhave, katā atthassa viññāpanāya."
msgstr "“I’ve made up this simile to make a point."

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ cevettha attho—"
msgstr "And this is what it means."

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.3"
msgid ""
"samatittiko telapattoti kho, bhikkhave, kāyagatāya etaṃ satiyā adhivacanaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘A bowl of oil filled to the brim’ is a term for mindfulness of the body."

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.4"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.5"
msgid ""
"‘kāyagatā sati no bhāvitā bhavissati bahulīkatā yānīkatā vatthukatā "
"anuṭṭhitā paricitā susamāraddhā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will develop mindfulness of the body. We’ll cultivate it, make it our "
"vehicle and our basis, keep it up, consolidate it, and properly implement "
"it.’"

msgctxt "sn47.20:3.6"
msgid "Evañhi kho, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.7"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.20:3.8"
msgid "Nālandavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.171"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.1"
msgid "Mahāpuriso nālandaṃ,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.2"
msgid "Cundo celañca bāhiyo;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.3"
msgid "Uttiyo ariyo brahmā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn47.20:4.4"
msgid "Sedakaṃ janapadena cāti."
msgstr ""
